    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Mechanical tension comes from the sheer struggle against heavy loads, like a truly difficult set where you feel deep in the muscle fiber.  Metabolic stress, conversely, is the \"burn\" caused by the buildup of metabolic byproducts like lactate during high-volume or high-rep work. Think of tension as the heavy strain on your muscles, while stress is the resulting fatigue and pump you feel. Optimal hypertrophy often involves hitting both these demanding areas in your training program.",
