      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "My apologies! I meant the **sarcomeres**, which are the functional contractile units like tiny repeating segments within the muscle fiber, not eyeballs. The cells sense tension through specialized mechanoreceptors, like titin or integrins, which act like cellular tension sensors. When a sarcomere stretches or is compressed under heavy weight, these structures deform, causing conformational changes that initiate intracellular signaling cascades. These pathways are what convert the raw physical force into biochemical signals encouraging muscle repair and growth.",
